\section{Numeric Scales}

Scale questions represent the common 
\enquote{rate this from one to five} style
interaction.  The labels are optional, but the range must be sensible.

<<classes>>=
@dataclass(frozen=True)
class ScaleQuestion:
    """A numeric scale question."""

    text: str
    low: int = 1
    high: int = 5
    low_label: str = ""
    high_label: str = ""
    kind: str = "scale"

    def __post_init__(self):
        if self.low >= self.high:
            raise ValueError("scale questions need low < high")

    def to_dict(self) -> dict[str, Any]:
        """Return a JSON-friendly representation of the question."""

        return {
            "kind": self.kind,
            "text": self.text,
            "low": self.low,
            "high": self.high,
            "low_label": self.low_label,
            "high_label": self.high_label,
        }
@

Again, the validation matters because every later component assumes a proper
closed interval:

<<test functions>>=
def test_scale_question_requires_ordered_bounds():
    with pytest.raises(ValueError):
        ScaleQuestion("Pace?", low=5, high=5)
